If you want to create a custom workflow, select `Custom Scenario`.""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "enum", "possible_values": ["Default Scenario", "Custom Scenario"], "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_additional_global_conversation_instruction` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_additional_global_conversation_instruction",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Conversation - Additional Global Conversation Instruction [C]", "description": """Additional instruction being injected into the conversational prompt.

This is the so-called \"Bart rule\" (a reference to The Simpsons series, where Bart writes on the
chalkboard over and over).

The value of this attribute is inserted into UserMessageReply in a highly visible place. As a
result, the Agent pays close attention to its content. However, this is a very dangerous attribute.
In fact, it should only be used in emergency situations when it is URGENTLY necessary to correct the
Agent's behavior.

**If there is too much information, it can lead to unexpected behavior.**

Ideally, this attribute should contain 2-3 sentences that clearly state what the agent will or will
not do.

Example:

```txt
I will always tell the price and mention that it may change. I will never ask about the user's birth date.
```""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_additional_limitations_and_restrictions` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_additional_limitations_and_restrictions",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Conversation - Additional Limitations and Restrictions [B]", "description": """These are any additional limitations and restrictions that the agent should consider during the
conversation, if applicable.

When communicating via chat, the agent does not observe the criteria for transferring a call to a
manager. However, these criteria essentially describe the agent's limitations to a significant
extent. This attribute enforces such limitations so that they are also observed in the chat.

Example for `restaurant` industry:

```txt
- Confirm that their table reservation is secured;
- Notify that they will be late for an existing reservation;
- Participate in or book a table for a special event mentioned in the context;
- Order catering;
- Report a forgotten or lost item at the restaurant;
- Speak with customer service;
```""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_blocked_phone_numbers` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_blocked_phone_numbers",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Phone - Blocked Numbers [A]", "description": """The \"blocked phone numbers\" field contains phone numbers that are not allowed to call the agent.

If a user calls from one of these specified phone numbers, the agent will end the call proactively.
When a user exceeds the configured spam limit (`project_attributes_setting_spam_limit`) of
consecutive spam sessions, their phone number is automatically added to this list.

**Example:**

```json
[\"13334445556\", \"12223334455\"]
```

**Format options (for each phone number in the list):**

- With plus: `+12223334444`
- Without plus: `12223334444`

Both formats are accepted, but make sure to include the full country code in all entries.""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "json", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_spam_limit` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_spam_limit",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Phone - Spam Limit [A]", "description": """The spam limit field defines the maximum number of consecutive spam sessions a persona can have
before their phone number is automatically added to
`project_attributes_setting_blocked_phone_numbers`.

**Important:** to disable automatic blocking by spam limit, set this value to `-1`.""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "number", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_booking_cancellation_enabled` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_booking_cancellation_enabled",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Booking - Cancellation - Enabled [B]", "description": """This setting enables or disables the booking cancellation feature.

When enabled, the agent can cancel appointments, reservations, etc.

It activates special observer who is helping ConvoAgent to check existing bookings and cancel.

Since the agent needs to know the booking ID, you must include the `id` parameter in the response to
the booking submission request.""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "bool", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_booking_cancellation_type` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_booking_cancellation_type",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Booking - Cancellation - Type [C]", "description": """This setting determines how the agent should handle a cancellation request.

There are three options:

- `default`: The system uses the standard booking cancellation method
- `endpoint`: The system uses an external endpoint for booking cancellation
- `project`: The system uses the project-specific method for booking cancellation

The `default` method works in the following way: the agent will try to look up a
`manage_booking_url` field among the existing user's booking and then send it to the user via SMS.
Important: currently, works only for the `restaurant` industry.

The `endpoint` method is used to send an HTTP request to a specified endpoint to cancel a booking.

The `project` method is used to trigger a system event to cancel a booking.""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "enum", "possible_values": ["default", "endpoint", "project"], "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_booking_cancellation_url` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_booking_cancellation_url",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Booking - Cancellation - URL [B]", "description": """This setting defines the URL to which the agent will send cancellation requests. The agent will send
a DELETE request to this URL with the booking ID as a part of the URL. Please note that the URL must
be a valid endpoint that can handle DELETE requests. The URL must include placeholder `{booking_id}`
which will be replaced with the actual booking ID. For example:
`https://example.com/bookings/{booking_id}`.""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

