{# #### `project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_processing_type` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_processing_type",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Booking - Check Availability - Processing Type [C]", "description": """This setting determines how the agent should handle a check availability request.

There are three options:

- `use_llm`: in case your response is not formatted, the agent will use LLM to understand
  availability from the response
- `formatted_response`: in case your response is formatted, the agent will use the response directly
- `custom`: you can use your custom flow to handle the availability response

If your system/project is able to respond back with the object compatible with the below schema,
please enable
`project_attributes_private_feature_flag_booking_use_new_availability_formatted_response_processor`
feature flag.

Schema:

```json
{
  \"type\": \"object\",
  \"title\": \"Availability Response Schema\",
  \"additionalProperties\": true,
  \"description\": \"Universal schema for availability across all industries\",
  \"required\": [\"availability\"],
  \"properties\": {
    \"range\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"description\": \"Human-readable time range (e.g., 'from 01:00 PM to 03:00 PM'). Optional for date-grouped responses. Example: `from 01:00 PM to 03:00 PM`\"
    },
    \"resourceType\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"description\": \"Type of resource being scheduled (optional, inferred if not provided). Examples: location, doctor.\"
    },
    \"availability\": {
      \"type\": \"array\",
      \"description\": \"List of resources with their available time slots\",
      \"items\": {
        \"type\": \"object\",
        \"required\": [\"availableTimeSlots\"],
        \"properties\": {
          \"location\": {
            \"type\": \"string\",
            \"description\": \"DEPRECATED: Use 'resource' instead. Kept for backwards compatibility. Can also represent a date (YYYY-MM-DD) for date-grouped availability.\"
          },
          \"resource\": {
            \"type\": \"string\",
            \"description\": \"Name/identifier of the resource (e.g., 'Dr. Smith', 'Patio', 'Team A', '2025-11-08')\"
          },
          \"availableTimeSlots\": {
            \"type\": \"array\",
            \"description\": \"List of available time slots in hh:mm AM/PM format. Examples: 09:00 AM, 05:00 PM\",
            \"items\": {
              \"type\": \"string\"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    \"targetAction\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"description\": \"Optional action identifier for workflow routing. Example: check_availability\"
    }
  }
}
```""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "enum", "possible_values": ["use_llm", "formatted_response", "custom"], "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_payload_schema_template` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_payload_schema_template",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Booking - Check Availability - Schema [C]", "description": """This setting defines the schema for booking availability requests.

The schema is a JSON object that specifies the structure of the booking availability request. It
must include the schema of the payload.

Please note if `project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_request_http_method` is set to
send `GET` request, the agent will build the URL with query parameters based on this attribute and
will add them to `project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_url`. If
`project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_request_http_method` is set to send `POST`
request, the agent will send the request body with the payload built based on this attribute.

This attribute supports \"templating\" - within the text of this attribute, values from other
attributes can be inserted. Special \"placeholders\" in the format [[attribute_name]] are used for
this purpose.

**Example for restaurants:**

```json
{
  \"type\": \"object\",
  \"properties\": {
    \"date\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"description\": \"User's preferred date for the reservation in format YYYY-MM-DD. Example: 2024-09-28\"
    },
    \"time\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"description\": \"User's preferred time for the reservation in format HH:MM (24 hours). Example: 20:00. If not provided, default to 19:00\",
      \"default\": \"19:00\"
    },
    \"dateTime\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"description\": \"User's preferred date and time for the reservation in format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM. Combine `date` and `time` properties in the format. Example: 2024-09-28 20:00\"
    },
    \"partySize\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"description\": \"Only one number, the number of people for the reservation, if a range is provided, is set to maximum. Example: 6\"
    },
    \"timeZone\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"enum\": [\"[[project_business_time_zone]]\"]
    },
    \"restaurantId\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"enum\": [\"[[project_attributes_private_dynamic_restaurant_google_restaurant_id]]\"]
    },
    \"timeFormat\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"enum\": [\"12\"]
    }
  },
  \"required\": [\"date\", \"time\", \"dateTime\", \"partySize\", \"timeZone\", \"restaurantId\", \"timeFormat\"]
}
```""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "json", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

