{# #### `project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_validation_schema_template` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_validation_schema_template",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Booking - Check Availability - Validation Schema [C]", "description": """This setting defines the schema for booking availability validation requests. The schema defines
fields that are used to validate the booking availability request.

To perform validation, the agent will check if the provided values are valid and meet the
requirements. So each field in the schema must be true, otherwise the agent will not proceed with
the booking and will let the user know that something is wrong.

**Example for restaurants:**

```json
{
  \"type\": \"object\",
  \"properties\": {
    \"regularGroup\": {
      \"type\": \"boolean\",
      \"description\": \"Set to true if **persons < [[project_attributes_restaurant_large_group_reservation_minimum_party_size]]**.\"
    }
  },
  \"required\": [\"regularGroup\"]
}
```""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "json", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_type` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_type",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Booking - Check Availability - Type [C]", "description": """This setting defines the type of availability check the agent can handle.

There are four options:

- `default`: The system uses the standard availability check method
- `endpoint`: The system uses an external endpoint to check availability
- `intercom`: The system uses intercom integration to check availability
- `project`: The system uses the project-specific method to check availability

The `default` method is recommended for most cases, as it is more reliable and provides better
integration with the booking system.

The `endpoint` method is used in specific cases where the standard method is not available or does
not provide accurate results.

The `intercom` method is used when the agent needs to check availability through intercom.

The `project` method is used when the agent needs to check availability through the project. In that
case the agent sends system event `get_available_slots`.""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior - Advanced", "value_type": "enum", "possible_values": ["default", "endpoint", "intercom", "project"], "is_hidden": True }
)}}

