{# #### `project_attributes_setting_session_ended_report_content` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_session_ended_report_content",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "5-05. Reports - Session Ended Report - Content [B] [IMPORTANT]", "description": """Specify the content of the report that will be generated upon session completion.

Agents can send reports to business management upon the completion of sessions (for instance, after
phone calls or live chat sessions).

In this attribute, you can define which types of sessions should trigger reports (you probably don't
want reports for spam calls) and what specific information should be included in the report
depending on the session type. For example, for a large group booking, you might want to see the
date and number of guests, while for a delivery order, you'd likely prefer the delivery address and
product details.

Agents can send reports via both email and SMS.

A convenient feature is that you can customize report content depending on the channel. For
instance, you can configure the agent to send reports for urgent orders via both SMS and email,
while standard order reports can be sent by email only.

**Note 1:** The specific email address and phone number for report delivery can be configured in the
field `project_attributes_setting_session_ended_report_criteria_template`.

**Note 2:** If you do not want the agent to send reports after sessions at all, set
`project_attributes_setting_session_ended_report_enabled` to `False`.

**Note 3:** Agents can create entries in a specialized Google Sheet named `Client Session Logs`, the
link to which is stored in the attribute `project_attributes_info_client_session_logs_table_link`.

**Note 4:** Agents can also create entries in your CRM or booking system. For assistance with
configuring this feature, please contact support.

Example:

```txt
## Report Type: **LARGE GROUP RESERVATION**

### Description:
The customer wants to book a large group party.

### Fields to be included in the report:
User name
User phone
User email
Party size
Requested date
Requested time
Special requests
40-word summary

### Subject line format:
Congratulations with a LARGE GROUP RESERVATION! [user name] [user phone] [12-word
additional summary]

### SMS example:
Congratulations! LARGE GROUP RESERVATION: [user name] [user phone] [20-word additional summary]
Truly, [agent name], [agent title]
```

**Important:** Attributes `project_attributes_setting_session_ended_report_content` and
`project_attributes_setting_session_ended_report_criteria_template` are highly related to each
other. Update them accordingly.""", "group": "5. Reports", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": False }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_session_ended_report_criteria_template` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_session_ended_report_criteria_template",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "5-06. Reports - Session Ended Report - Criteria [B] [IMPORTANT]", "description": """Set a template of criteria to be used for generating a report upon session completion.

This attribute defines the \"template\" for the report generated after the conversation ends. The word
\"template\" indicates that within the text of this attribute, values from other attributes can be
inserted. Special \"placeholders\" in the format [[attribute_name]] are used for this purpose. When
the conversation ends, the system automatically replaces these placeholders with real data and
generates the final report. As a result, this attribute allows you to receive a completed report
text with all the necessary data in the appropriate places. You must include names from Intent Types
column from Workflow Builder. Otherwise, your reports won't be sent.

Example:

```txt
**Criteria for SMS Report:**
- **During working hours:**
  - If it is a Manager or Human Request send an SMS to +12223334444
  - If it is a Large Reservation or Cancel Reservation, send an SMS to the
    [[project_business_working_hour_escalation_phone]]
  - If it is a Guest Support or Contractor support send an SMS to [[project_business_working_hour_escalation_phone]]
- **Outside working hours:**
  - If it is a Human or Manager Request, send an SMS to +12223334444
---
**Criteria for Email Report:**
- If it is a Manager or Human Request, send an email to emergency@email.example
- If it is a Large Reservation, Cancel Reservation, Reschedule or modification, send an email to
  [[project_business_manager_email]]
- If it is a Guest Support or Contractor Support send an email to [[project_business_manager_email]]
```

You can also include any amount of additional receiver email addresses in the form of `cc`. Use the
following example:

```txt
...
**Criteria for Email Report:**
- If it is a Manager or Human Request, send an email to [[project_business_manager_email]] and cc to [[project_business_top_owner_email]], [[your_custom_attribute_name_with_email_address]]
- If it is a Large Reservation, Cancel Reservation, Reschedule or modification, send an email to
  [[project_business_manager_email]] and cc to your-first-additional-email@example.com, your-second-additional-email@example.com
- If it is a Guest Support or Contractor Support, send an email to [[project_business_manager_email]] and cc to your-third-additional-email@example.com
...

```

You can also include any amount of additional receiver phone numbers in the form of `sms`. Use the
following example:

```txt
...
**Criteria for SMS Report:**
- If it is a Manager or Human Request, send an SMS to [[project_business_working_hour_escalation_phone]] and +12223334445
- If it is a Large Reservation, Cancel Reservation, Reschedule or modification, send an SMS to +12223334444 and +12223334446
...

```

**Important:**

- To add, remove fields or modify email subject / sms body templates, use Reports - Session Ended
  Report (`project_attributes_setting_session_ended_report_content`)
- Double square brackets are used to inject attribute value. Use `[[..]]` format to specify the
  attribute name. For example, `[[project_business_manager_email]]` will be replaced with the value
  of the `project_business_manager_email` attribute. So if you want to specify some email or phone
  number which is not an attribute, specify it as is, without square brackets (see the example with
  `+12223334444` and `emergency@email.example` mentioned above).""", "group": "5. Reports", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": False }
)}}

