{# ### 5. reports - advanced Attributes #}

{# #### `project_attributes_private_custom_schema_inbound_call_report` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_private_custom_schema_inbound_call_report",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Reports - Phone Inbound - Custom Schema [C]", "description": """This setting helps to capture important details from a conversation automatically at the end of a
session. It extends the list of values that the agent extracts from the conversation by default.

**How it works:**

- A predefined `template (schema)` tells the system what information to look for in the conversation
- If a detail is mentioned by the user, it is captured and stored
- If a detail is missing, the system sets it to `Not Provided` instead of leaving it blank
- All collected details are saved in session logs, making it easy to access and analyze later

**Example of schema used for data extraction:**

```json
{
  \"type\": \"object\",
  \"properties\": {
    \"organization\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"description\": \"Set to the organization name provided by the user. If the user didn't mention an organization name, set it to \\\"Not Provided\\\".\"
    },
    \"job_title\": {
      \"type\": \"string\",
      \"description\": \"Job title provided by the user. If the user didn't mention a job title, set it to \\\"Not Provided\\\".\"
    }
  },
  \"required\": [\"organization\", \"job_title\"]
}
```

**Example of what it captures:**

If a user shares their company name and job title during the conversation, the system records:

- Organization: \"ABC Corp\"
- Job Title: \"Marketing Manager\"

If they don't mention this information, the system saves:

- Organization: \"Not Provided\"
- Job Title: \"Not Provided\"

**Why it is useful**

- Saves important details automatically
- Ensures no critical information is missed
- Organizes data clearly for future use

This makes it easy to review past conversations and use the captured information for reports,
insights, or follow-ups.""", "group": "5. Reports - Advanced", "value_type": "json", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_asr_recognition` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_asr_recognition",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "ASR - Working Hours Recognition [A]", "description": """This is a **normalization coefficient** used to estimate what portion of all deals closed by the AI
Receptionist can be attributed **exclusively to the AI Receptionist** (i.e. the deals that would
have been lost before the AI Receptionist was implemented).

Businesses lose a different percentage of deals depending on the time of day.

- **Non-working hours**. During non-working hours, we assume—simplified—that the business used to
  lose **100% of deals**. Therefore, all deals that the AI Receptionist now closes during
  non-working hours are considered **fully attributable to the AI Receptionist**. As a result, for
  non-working hours this coefficient is set to **100%**.
- **Working hours.** During working hours, by default we assume that, on average, businesses used to
  lose **about 30% of deals** because they could not respond to inquiries fast enough.

However, note that the value of this normalization coefficient depends on the **Redirection Type**:

- **For overflow mode (\"first-human-then-AI\")**: This coefficient is set to **100%**, because in
  this mode the AI Receptionist only handles calls that the human staff have already missed.
  Therefore, all deals closed by the AI Receptionist in this mode are considered **fully its
  achievement**.
- **For non-overflow mode (\"first-AI-then-human\")**: In this mode, the AI Receptionist handles **all
  deals** for the business — both the ones the human staff used to close successfully before
  implementation and the ones they used to lose. Therefore, only the share of deals that were
  previously lost should be attributed exclusively to the AI Receptionist.

For example, suppose the AI Receptionist closes 10 deals in this mode. Before its implementation,
suppose human colleagues used to close 7 of those 10 and lose 3. So it would be incorrect to
consider all 10 as additional revenue. In this case, we apply a **30% coefficient**, meaning that
only **30% of the 10 deals** are considered exclusively attributable to the AI Receptionist.""", "group": "5. Reports - Advanced", "value_type": "number", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

